  ResumeScreener Pro — Offline Edition
  100% Local · No API · No Internet Required to Run
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  HOW TO RUN — STEP BY STEP
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

OPTION 1 — Double Click (Easiest)
  1. Extract / unzip this folder anywhere on your computer
  2. Open the folder → double-click "index.html"
  3. It will open in your default browser → Done!

  ⚠️  NOTE: PDF reading requires a local server (see Option 2).
      If you only want to paste text, Option 1 works fine.

──────────────────────────────────────────

OPTION 2 — Local Server (Recommended for PDF Upload)
  PDF files need a local HTTP server to be read by the browser.
  Pick whichever method you have available:

  ── Python (installed on Mac/Linux by default) ──
  1. Open Terminal
  2. cd into this folder:
       cd /path/to/ResumeScreener-Pro
  3. Run:
       python3 -m http.server 8080
  4. Open browser → go to:
       http://localhost:8080

  ── Node.js ──
  1. Open Terminal in this folder
  2. Run:
       npx serve .
  3. Open the URL shown (usually http://localhost:3000)

  ── VS Code ──
  1. Open this folder in VS Code
  2. Install "Live Server" extension (Ritwick Dey)
  3. Right-click index.html → "Open with Live Server"

  ── XAMPP / WAMP / MAMP ──
  1. Place this folder in your htdocs/www folder
  2. Start Apache
  3. Go to: http://localhost/ResumeScreener-Pro/

──────────────────────────────────────────

OPTION 3 — Text Paste (No Server Needed)
  If you don't want to set up a server:
  1. Open your resume PDF in any PDF viewer
  2. Select All (Ctrl+A) → Copy (Ctrl+C)
  3. In the app, paste into the "Or Paste Resume Text" box
  4. Select your domain and click Analyze → works instantly!

