  BROWSER COMPATIBILITY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  ✅ Chrome 90+       (recommended)
  ✅ Firefox 88+
  ✅ Edge 90+
  ✅ Safari 14+
  ✅ Opera 76+
  ❌ Internet Explorer (not supported)

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  PRIVACY
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Your resume is read locally in the browser.
  No data is sent to any server.
  No API calls are made.
  Nothing is stored after you close the tab.
  Internet is only needed to load Google Fonts
  and PDF.js (one-time on first load).

  To run 100% offline after first load:
  The browser will cache fonts and PDF.js automatically.
  After that, it works with airplane mode on.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  TROUBLESHOOTING
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

  Problem: "Could not read text from PDF"
  Reason:  Your PDF is scanned (image-based, not text)
  Fix:     Copy-paste your resume text into the text box

  Problem: PDF upload does nothing / file reading fails
  Reason:  Browser blocks local file:// PDF access
  Fix:     Use Option 2 (local server) above

  Problem: Fonts look wrong
  Reason:  No internet connection to load Google Fonts
  Fix:     Load the page once with internet, then cache kicks in

  Problem: Analysis score seems off
  Reason:  Rule-based scoring is approximate — results vary
           based on how your resume text is formatted
  Fix:     Paste text manually for better extraction accuracy

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
  QUICK START COMMANDS
